<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9574] ConcurrentModificationException in Java9.concealedPackageList</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9574</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Facing the following exception in a multithreaded environment with multiple threads executing the same Groovy code (@CompileStatic is not used). HashMap is not reentrant, but computeIfAbsent may insert an element if a key is missing. If another thread is iterating through the map at the same time, I can see why this exception is being raised. Is the fix as simple as replacing HashMap with ConcurrentHashMap, or are there performance implications?&lt;/p&gt;
